
Include amon.py in your path and run:

   amon.py <.alist file name>  <.vex file name>

Alternatively without setting up paths use wrapper script amon.sh,
which also copies the default amon_config when no custom config is present
in the current working directory:

   amon.sh <.alist file name>  <.vex file name>


To run, this version of AMON must include the following files (all files except amon.py
are placed in two subdirectories, amon_lib and amon_config):

amon.py                                                                  main script
amon_lib: amon_lib.py, vex_parser_lib.py, plt_lbls_lib.py, __init__.py   libraries

amon_config/amon_config.txt                                              the configuration file
amon_config/amon_help.txt (this name can be changed in the config file)  this help file
amon_config/eht_codes     (this name can be changed in the config file)  one letter - two letter
                                                                         antenna code
                                                                         correspondence file
